<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND
        CRANKCASE - OIL LEVEL GAUGE TUBE ASSEMBLY - INSTALLATION (Refer to Figure 7.25)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>INSTALLATION (Refer to Figure 7.25)</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the lower oil level gauge tube into the crankcase orifice as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Apply Loctite(r) #609 around entire circumference of tube and casting.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Press tube in until the bead is seated in chamber of the crankcase.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The slots in oil level gauge tube need not be oriented in any special manner.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new O-Ring gasket onto oil level filler tube.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert oil level filler tube into oil level gauge tube and orient oil filler tube to the
                rear and as far inboard as possible.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten oil filler tube clamp screw to the special torque value.</para>
            <figure id="ef1050725" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg2378" filename="../figeg2/EG2378.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.25.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Tube Clamp</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Oil Filler Tube</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Oil Level Gauge</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. Oil Level Gauge Lower Tube</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. Crankcase</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
